  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "12 more arrests for 9th May violence",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "COLOMBO (News 1st); Sri Lanka Police arrested 12 more suspects in connection to the violence that broke out on the 9th of May 2022.",
        "04 suspects were arrested by the Kegalle police in connection with the attack on the residence and office of parliamentarian Tharaka Balasuriya in Kegalle.",
        "A 58-year-old suspect was arrested in connection with the attacks on the residences of Parliamentarians Rohitha Abeygunawardena and Johnston Fernando.",
        "Two residents of Mahawa and Kahatagasdigiliya areas were arrested in connection with an incident of assaulting the Chairman of the Elahera Pradeshiya Sabha.",
        "Another suspect was arrested for damaging the residence of MP Vidura Wickramanayake, while one suspect was arrested for causing damages to the residences of Arundhika Fernando, and the Chairperson of the Mahara Pradeshiya Sabha.",
        "One-month-old infant abandoned at a motor garage with a letter",
        "Are you a victim of Cyber Crime? Police Unit ready to crackdown crime in the cyberspace"
      ],
